v2.0.12 La Víbora Edition candidate release.

New: In stock.zul now is possible to force the quantity of an item. The corresponding decimal box now allows writes in it.
	Owner right must be granted to the user. A Configuration object modify decision is made with the argument:
	
	tt_Stock_tt tt_MODIFIED_BY_tt <loginname>. 
	tt_Warehouse_tt : <warehouseid>. 
	tt_Item_tt : <inventoryitemcode>. 
	tt_NewStockQuantity_tt : <inventoryitemquantity>.
	
	The database function is:
	
	 FUNCTION soberano."fn_Business_forceStockQuantityAdjusment"(warehouseid integer,
														inventoryitemcode character varying,
														inventoryitemquantity numeric,
														loginname character varying)
 

New: USB/Bluetooth raw printing. No CUPS needed for printing directly through USB/Bluetooth devices. In WEB-INF/docs 
	folder, there is a note explaining how to configure a symlink (USB case) allowing the printer to get safely unplugged 
	and plugged again, or connected to another port, and still keeping a persistent identifier. In WEB-INF/docs folder, 
	ther is also a note explaining the bluetooth case.
	
New: Now is possible to configure a print method a printer profile uses. Options are: PDF, PNG, RAW. This can be done by means of
	printer profiles configuration form (printer_profiles.zul).
	
New: Stock records deletion on FUNCTION soberano."fn_Business_clean". Stock records are created upon shift closures.
	"StockRecord" is one of the largest relations of the database.

New: Custom report 4 added.
	
